<% content_for(:title) { "Pricing" } %>
<% content_for(:meta_description) { "mbuzz pricing: free tier plus Starter ($29), Growth ($99), and Pro ($299) per month. Event-based, overage transparent, no contracts. Cancel any time." } %>
<% content_for(:og_title) { "mbuzz Pricing — Server-Side Attribution from $0" } %>
<% content_for(:canonical_url) { pricing_url } %>

<% content_for :head do %>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    <%= {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Product",
      name: App::PUBLISHER_NAME,
      description: "Multi-touch attribution that shows the model behind the number. Eight models side-by-side, a SQL-like DSL for custom models, open-source SDKs.",
      brand: { "@type": "Brand", name: App::PUBLISHER_NAME },
      offers: {
        "@type": "AggregateOffer",
        priceCurrency: "USD",
        lowPrice: "0",
        highPrice: "299",
        offerCount: 4,
        offers: [
          { "@type": "Offer", name: "Free", price: "0", priceCurrency: "USD", description: "30,000 events/month. Full access to all 8 attribution models. No custom DSL models." },
          { "@type": "Offer", name: "Starter", price: "29", priceCurrency: "USD", description: "1,000,000 events/month. 3 custom DSL attribution models. Overage: $5 per 250,000 events." },
          { "@type": "Offer", name: "Growth", price: "99", priceCurrency: "USD", description: "5,000,000 events/month. 5 custom DSL attribution models. Overage: $15 per 1,000,000 events." },
          { "@type": "Offer", name: "Pro", price: "299", priceCurrency: "USD", description: "25,000,000 events/month. 10 custom DSL attribution models. Overage: $50 per 5,000,000 events." }
        ]
      }
    }.to_json.html_safe %>
  </script>
<% end %>

<%= render "layouts/nav" %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-white">
  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">
        Start free. Pay for events, not seats.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Every plan includes all eight attribution models, the Attribution DSL for writing your own,
        and open-source SDKs for Ruby, Node, Python, and PHP. You pay for the events you track.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base text-gray-500">
        No contracts. No sales calls. Cancel any time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%= render "pages/home/pricing" %>

  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">How pricing works</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What's an event?</h3>
          <p>
            One tracked touchpoint in a customer journey: a pageview, a click, a signup, a purchase,
            or any custom event you send to the mbuzz API. Events feed into the attribution models.
            The more events you track, the more complete the journey mbuzz can reconstruct.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What happens if I go over my plan limit?</h3>
          <p>
            Paid plans (Starter / Growth / Pro) have a transparent overage rate per additional block of events:
            $5 per 250K on Starter, $15 per 1M on Growth, $50 per 5M on Pro. You keep tracking,
            we charge the overage at the end of the billing period. No surprise invoices, no hard cutoffs.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The Free tier hard-caps at 30,000 events. No overage — events beyond the cap are dropped
            until the next billing cycle or you upgrade.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What are custom DSL models?</h3>
          <p>
            mbuzz ships with eight attribution models (first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay,
            position-based, Markov, Shapley, data-driven). If none of them match how your business
            actually works, you can write your own in the Attribution DSL — a SQL-like language for
            defining attribution logic. Free includes 0, Starter 3, Growth 5, Pro 10.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Do I own my data?</h3>
          <p>
            Yes. Every plan includes CSV export, API access, and an MCP server for agent-native
            pulls. No premium-tier gate on data export, no vendor lock-in. Fork the open-source
            SDKs and keep running if you ever leave.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Is there an annual discount?</h3>
          <p>
            Not yet. Pricing is month-to-month because bootstrap-stage customers shouldn't have to
            commit a year ahead to get a fair rate. We'll reconsider when the product hits its next
            tier of maturity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Enterprise?</h3>
          <p>
            If you need more than 25M events/month, custom integrations, or a commercial agreement,
            <%= link_to "get in touch", contact_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline" %>
            and we'll scope something. No MSA theatre, just a conversation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-blue-600">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Start tracking in minutes
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-blue-100 mb-8">
        Free tier. No credit card. No sales call. SDKs for Ruby, Node, Python, and PHP.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
        <%= link_to "Get Started Free", signup_path, class: "px-8 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-blue-600 bg-white hover:bg-blue-50 rounded-md transition-all" %>
        <%= link_to "Read the Docs", docs_path('getting-started'), class: "px-8 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-white border border-white/30 hover:bg-white/10 rounded-md transition-all" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<%= render "layouts/footer" %>
